Date: 0/0/1939
Source: Outside the Law
Author: BELTON
Vol / Page: 142
Edition:
Quote: The [confidence trick] probably best known ... is the `Spanish Prisoner' ... [A letter is written to the victim ... intimating that the writer is prisoner in gaol and has a sum of money hidden, which he can get if he has ready cash to bribe warders and get out. He asks the victim for money to do this, promising to return it with a bonus.]
